\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing access exclusions**\\n\\nI'm wondering why the dynamic access analyzer might exclude `com.sun.tools.javac.Main`. It seems to list class$ only, which leads me to think it may not cover the custom-loaded CompilerAdapterFactory class. Could this be an issue with coverage instrumentation? I want to dig a little deeper into this to understand what’s happening. There’s definitely some complexity here, and I want to make sure I'm not missing something important in the analysis.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented a dedicated test file for the active class:\n\n- Added `tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java/ant/ant/CompilerAdapterFactoryTest.java`\n\nCoverage added for `CompilerAdapterFactory` dynamic-access paths:\n\n- Resolves a fully qualified compiler adapter class name through `CompilerAdapterFactory.getCompiler(...)`, exercising:\n  - `resolveClassName` `Class.forName(...)`\n  - `resolveClassName` `Class.newInstance()`\n\n- Uses an isolated class loader that hides `com.sun.tools.javac.Main` to force the modern compiler fallback path, exercising:\n  - the synthetic `class$` `Class.forName(...)` call associated with `CompilerAdapterFactory.class`\n\nThe Native Image unsupported dynamic-class-loading case is handled with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(...)` as requested.\n\nI did not compile or run tests, per your instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_042e5b8834f6a4fe0169f560d5877881a194ccd7d227d4b2ef\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 659, "output": 1096, "cacheRead": 35328, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37083, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777688776264, "responseId": "resp_042e5b8834f6a4fe0169f560c8b95c81a18eb0f66684209b98"}}
