ages the factory, and while line 178 is in the child, it seems coverage isn't working as expected. Maybe the coverage tool only records call sites in the original classloader since it lists the currently loaded library jars by the system. Creating a custom system classloader doesn’t seem feasible.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test structure**\\n\\nI’m evaluating whether to create a test helper in the same package under src/test/java/org/apache/... The rule states to keep tests outside the library's packages and not to place a test in the same package. But if I create a helper, it should technically be outside the top-level test class. So, I need to consider if this approach adheres to the guidelines while still being useful for the tests. Let’s think this through!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating method invocation**\\n\\nI’m considering whether the line mapping in the report is wrong. It seems that the method at line 178 is only invoked by `doesModernCompilerExist`. The direct invocation shows frame class$, but instrumentation might check the caller chain for `doesModernCompilerExist`. So, I might need to clear a static field before invoking `getCompiler(\\\"modern\\\")`, especially in cases where the first class forName fails. There's no way to hide javac, so I need to think this through.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_snaokW8A52jH5qEOzVCT7Vx9|fc_042e5b8834f6a4fe0169f56226b2c081a1a9ecdd29f0f554ee", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"lookupCompilerGeneratedClass|classLookupMethod|class\\$\" tests/src -g '*Test.java' | head -100"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1837, "output": 2372, "cacheRead": 34816, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39025, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777689092851, "responseId": "resp_042e5b8834f6a4fe0169f562056bbc81a191b749f5f860de7c"}